cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper proposes a new approach to mitigate DDoS attacks, which is a common problem in network security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the efficiency of router operation, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions new business opportunities for ISPs, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
